Description: CVE-2026-33845 - Fix integer underflow in DTLS handshake fragment reassembly
 A flaw in GnuTLS DTLS handshake parsing allows malformed fragments with
 zero length and non-zero offset, leading to an integer underflow during
 reassembly and resulting in an out-of-bounds read. This is remotely
 exploitable and may cause denial of service.
 .
 Instead of maintaining an inclusive [start_offset, end_offset] range
 when reassembling DTLS handshake, track start_offset and a relative
 frag_length instead. This fixes 0-length fragments triggering completion
 if message was 1 byte long and a remotely triggerable underflow with an
 ensuing heap overrun.
Origin: upstream, https://gitlab.com/gnutls/gnutls/-/commit/e5b72c53c7d789d19d1d1cd10b275e87d0415413
Author: Alexander Sosedkin <asosedkin@redhat.com>
Last-Update: 2026-05-01

