Description: CVE-2026-42010 - Fix PSK username NUL-character matching
 A server looking up PSK username with a NUL-character in it was
 wrongfully matching username truncated at a NUL-character.
 Fix the check to compare up to the full username length by using
 info->username_len instead of strlen(info->username).
Origin: upstream, https://gitlab.com/gnutls/gnutls/-/commit/cb1833afd9b6309563211b1c0a7c291f52ca98d5
Author: Alexander Sosedkin <asosedkin@redhat.com>
Last-Update: 2026-05-08

